elationship with God), to the Father is through Jesus Christ. John 14:6</li>\n	<li>We believe the only way to enter heaven (eternal life) is through faith in Jesus Christ. Romans 10:9-11</li>\n	<li>We believe that the only way to salvation (freedom from eternal judgment) is by Gods grace, through Jesus Christ. Ephesians 2:8-9</li>\n	<li>We believe that without faith (opposite of works) it is impossible to please God. Hebrews 11:6</li>\n	<li>We believe that faith without works is dead (useless) and that works without faith is dead (useless). James 2:14-24</li>\n	<li>We believe that Jesus emptied Himself (stripped Himself) of His Godhead (deity) and humbled Himself as a man on earth. Philippians 2:6-11</li>\n	<li>We believe Jesus did nothing on earth (performing countless miracles and healings) as God, but as a man, anointed of the Holy Spirit. Luke 4:1, 14, John 5:19.</li>\n	<li>We believe that we (the Body of Christ), His disciples, are all commissioned to heal the sick, raise the dead, cleanse the lepers (heal diseases) and cast out demons. Mark 16: 15-20, Matthew 10:1,8, Mark 6:7,12-13, John 14:12-14, 15:7, 15:16, 16:23, 17:18 , Ephesians 4:11-16, Acts 5:12-16, 1st John 4:17, 3:2</li>\n	<li>We believe that all believers (all those that claim Jesus Christ as their Savior and Lord) will do even greater works (miracles, healings, signs and wonders ) than Jesus did. John 14:12</li>\n	<li>We believe that we as believers were sent, just like Jesus was sent to the earth, to destroy all the works of the devil and to enforce satan\'s defeat. John 17:18, 1st John 3:8</li>\n	<li>We believe that our power source to enforce satan\'s defeat, is only through the promise of the  Father, the Holy Spirit. Acts 2:33</li>\n	<li>We believe if any person does not possess the Holy Spirit, that they do not belong to Jesus Christ, that they are nottrulya child of God. Romans 8:9, 14 (Amplified)</li>\n	<li>We believe that relationship with Holy Spirit, and the use of His gifts is what marks the New Testament church (His Children) as His own. John 16:7, John 14:26, 1st Corinthians 12, 2nd Timothy 3:5</li>\n	<li>We believe that faith should only be in Gods Word, His logos (the written Word) and His rhema, the living Word, Jesus Christ. Hebrews 4:12, John 1:1-14</li>\n</ol>\nAccording to John 17:18 just as Jesus was sent to the earth by the Father, we also are sent into the world. Jesus perfectly represented the Father (John 17:6 ) in the world, demonstrating His outrageous grace and love for mankind, through healing the sick, raising the dead, cleansing the lepers and casting out demons. Just as Jesus represented the Father, now we are to perfectly represent the Son, by doing exactly what He did. Jesus was our supreme example of what His Body is to do on this earth, to represent Him. We too are sent to destroy the works of the devil, through intimate relationship with Holy Spirit, by healing the sick, raising the dead, cleansing the lepers and casting out demons. The core truth of the simple message of the gospel is revival, the manifestation of Gods love and power over all the power of the enemy. We are here to enforce satan\'s defeat at every turn.','What We Believe','','inherit','open','open','','40-autosave','','','2011-06-19 23:34:11','2011-06-19 23:34:11','',40,'http://greaterworkshealing.com/2011/06/40-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(213,1,'2011-06-10 04:01:13','2011-06-10 04:01:13','<ol>\r\n	<li>We believe Jesus Christ is not only the Son of God, but came to earth as God in the flesh. John 1:1-14</li>\r\n	<li>We believe the only way ( relationship with God ), to the Father is through Jesus Christ. John 14:6</li>\r\n	<li>We believe the only way to enter heaven, ( eternal life ) is through faith in Jesus Christ. Romans 10:9-11</li>\r\n	<li>We believe that the only way to salvation, ( freedom from eternal judgment ) is by Gods grace, through Jesus Christ. Ephesians 2:8-9</li>\r\n	<li>We believe that without faith, ( opposite of works ), it is impossible to please God. Hebrews 11:6</li>\r\n	<li>We believe that faith without works is dead,( useless ), and that works without faith is dead, ( useless ). James 2:14-24</li>\r\n	<li>We believe that Jesus emptied Himself,( stripped Himself ) of His Godhead, ( deity ), and humbled Himself as a man on earth. Philippians 2:6-11</li>\r\n	<li>We believe Jesus did nothing on earth, ( performing countless miracles and healings ), as God, but as a man, anointed of the Holy Spirit. Luke 4:1, 14, John 5:19.</li>\r\n	<li>We believe that we, ( the Body of Christ ), His disciples, are all commissioned to heal the sick, raise the dead, cleanse the lepers, ( heal diseases ), &amp;, to cast out demons. Mark 16: 15-20, Matthew 10:1,8, Mark 6:7,12-13, John 14:12-14, 15:7, 15:16, 16:23, 17:18 , Ephesians 4:11-16, Acts 5:12-16, 1st John 4:17, 3:2</li>\r\n	<li>We believe that we, all believers, ( all those that claim Jesus Christ as their Savior and Lord ), will do even greater works ( miracles, healings, signs, &amp;, wonders ) than Jesus did. John 14:12</li>\r\n	<li>We believe that we as believers were sent, just like Jesus was sent to the earth, to destroy all the works of the devil, and to enforce satins defeat. John 17:18, 1st John 3:8</li>\r\n	<li>We believe that our power source to enforce satins defeat, is only through the promise of the  Father, the Holy Spirit. Acts 2:33</li>\r\n	<li>We believe if we, ( any person ) does not possess the Holy Spirit, that they do not belong to Jesus Christ, that they are not trliy a child of God. Romans 8:9, 14. ( Amplified ).</li>\r\n	<li>We believe that relationship with Holy Spirit, and the use of His gifts, is what marks the New Testament church,( His Children ), as His own. John 16:7, John 14:26, 1st Corinthians 12, 2nd Timothy 3:5</li>\r\n	<li>We believe that faith sholid only be in Gods Word, His logos, ( the written Word ) and His rhema, the living Word, ( Jesus Christ ). Hebrews 4:12, John 1:1-14</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nAccording to John 17:18, Just as Jesus was sent to the earth by the Father, we also are sent into the world. Jesus perfectly represented the Father, (John 17:6 ), in the world, demonstrating His outrageous grace and love for mankind, through healing the sick, raising the dead, cleansing the lepers and casting out demons. Just as Jesus represented the Father, now we are to perfectly represent the Son, by doing exactly what He did. Jesus was our supreme example of what His Body is to do on this earth, to represent Him. We too are sent to destroy the works of the devil, through intimate relationship with Holy Spirit, by healing the sick, raising the dead, cleansing the lepers and casting out demons. The core truth of the simple message of the gospel is revival, the manifestation of Gods love and power over all the power of the enemy. We are here to enforce satins defeat at every turn.','What We Believe','','inherit','open','open','','40-revision-4','','','2011-06-10 04:01:13','2011-06-10 04:01:13','',40,'http://greaterworkshealing.com/2011/06/40-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(180,1,'2011-06-09 04:10:19','2011-06-09 04:10:19','Healing rooms','Online Healing Rooms','','inherit','open','open','','28-revision-3','','','2011-06-09 04:10:19','2011-06-09 04:10:19','',28,'http://greaterworkshealing.com/2011/06/28-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(304,2,'2011-07-14 21:27:49','2011-07-14 21:27:49','The spirit of Revival has been released across the globe. On July 23rd 2010 Revival broke out in Mobile Alabama as a woman who was paralyzed for 22 years began to walk. We had the privilege of attending this revival for nearly two months. We saw multiple healings and miracles. We watched as Lady Delia Knox walked and praised God on the platform for her miracle.\n\nDutch Sheets was speaking one night and declared this Revival a genuine awakening. 10 years before this Revival broke out someone asked Pastor Yonggi Cho where the last great Revival would break out. He reportedly turned to a globe of the earth and pointed to Mobile Bay, ( named Bay of Holy Spirit by the Spaniards ), and said it would begin here. It indeed has begun.\n\nWhile attending the conference I had a vision of tsunami wave of the blood of Jesus rolling across the land. Satan was standing there holding a toothpick up, trying to hold back the waves. He of course he could not. I also saw Revival breaking out in Wyoming. I saw a huge cross at the eastern side of the state overshadowing the entire state, from east to west, with the four corners of the cross touching the four borders of the state. Suddenly the cross spontaneously combusted and smoke poured from the cross. From the east came the wind of His Spirit and it blew the smoke of His presence across the entire state.\n\nI believe that the Spirit of Revival has been released in the earth and that God is looking for someone who actually believes that greater is He that is in you than he that is in the word to rise up and begin to act like it. Every since we left Alabama last December God has had us traveling all over the Northwest releasing Revival where ever we go. Go God!!!!','The Spirit of Revival','','inherit','open','open','','303-revision','','','2011-07-14 21:27:49','2011-07-14 21:27:49','',303,'http://greaterworkshealing.com/2011/07/303-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(182,1,'2011-06-12 21:18:01','2011-06-12 21:18:01','Greater Works was founded by <a title=\"Mark &amp; Cathy\" href=\"http://greaterworkshealing.com/about/mark-cathy/\">Mark and Cathy Kuntz</a>.  We have a vision to usher in the end time healing harvest by teaching people how to walk in divine healing, minister healing to others, do market place ministry and leading teams out on the streets to heal, save and deliver.  We are very passionate about revival, miracles and healings and believe the core of the gospel is revival and restoration of the entire man, spirit, soul and body.\n\nWe have also helped establish worldwide <a title=\"Connect\" href=\"http://healingrooms.com/index.p